he \"just started laughing\" upon hearing Bryant's comment and thought the 1992 team would win by double digits.<ref name=espn20120712>{{cite web|url=http://espn.go.com/olympics/summer/2012/basketball/story/_/id/8158008/charles-barkley-says-1992-dream-team-beat-2012-olympic-team-double-digits|title=Charles Barkley fires back at Kobe|date=July 11, 2012|accessdate=July 12, 2012|work=ESPN.com|publisher=ESPN Internet Ventures}}</ref> [[Michael Jordan]] added: \"For [Bryant] to compare those two teams is not one of the smarter things he ever could have done... Remember now, they learned from us. We didn't learn from them\".<ref>{{cite web|url=http://espn.go.com/olympics/summer/2012/basketball/story/_/id/8159879/2012-olympics-michael-jordan-laughed-kobe-bryant-dream-team-boast|title=Michael Jordan: Dream Team better|date=July 12, 2012|accessdate=July 12, 2012|work=ESPN.com|publisher=ESPN Internet Ventures}}</ref><ref>{{cite news|title=Michael Jordan: Dream Team could take down this year's team|url=https://www.usatoday.com/sports/olympics/london/basketball/story/2012-07-12/michael-jordan-kobe-bryant-dream-team-olympics/56170692/1|publisher=USA Today|date=July 12, 2012|accessdate=12 July 2012}}</ref> Bird joked, \"They probably could. I haven't played in 20 years and we're all old now.\"<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.sportsgrid.com/nba/larry-bird-dream-team-kobe-response/|title=Larry Bird Is Also Laughing At Kobe Bryant Over His Dream Team Comments|date=July 12, 2012}}</ref> Bryant later clarified that he thought the 1992 team was better, but it was \"ludicrous\" to think his team could not beat the Dream Team in one game.<ref name=stein_magic>{{cite news|last=Stein |first=Marc |title=Magic Johnson lauds London squad |date=August 3, 2012 |work=ESPN.com |url=http://espn.go.com/olympics/summer/2012/basketball/story/_/id/8229564/london-olympics-1992-dream-teamers-laud-2012-team-efforts |archiveurl=https://www.webcitation.org/69vQQj70z?url=http://espn.go.com/olympics/summer/2012/basketball/story/_/id/8229564/london-olympics-1992-dream-teamers-laud-2012-team-efforts |archivedate=August 15, 2012 |url-status=live }}</ref><ref>{{cite news|last=Smith |first=Erick |title=Kobe Bryant says Dream Team was better than '12 Olympic team |date=July 28, 2012 |newspaper=USA Today |url=https://www.usatoday.com/sports/olympics/london/basketball/story/2012-07-28/kobe-bryant-clarifies-dream-team-better/56556032/1 |archiveurl=https://www.webcitation.org/69vQX6IX2?url=http://www.usatoday.com/sports/olympics/london/basketball/story/2012-07-28/kobe-bryant-clarifies-dream-team-better/56556032/1 |archivedate=August 15, 2012 |url-status=live }}</ref> \"You didn't ask me if we could beat them in a 7-game series\", he said.<ref>{{cite news|last=Golliver|first=Ben|title=Kobe Bryant on Michael Jordan's trash talk: 'He knows I'm a bad mother[expletive]'|date=July 13, 2012|work=CBSSports.com|url=http://www.cbssports.com/nba/eye-on-basketball/19574539/kobe-bryant-responds-to-michael-jordans-trash-talk-he-knows-im-a-bad-motherexpletive|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20140214083626/http://www.cbssports.com/nba/eye-on-basketball/19574539/kobe-bryant-responds-to-michael-jordans-trash-talk-he-knows-im-a-bad-motherexpletive|archivedate=February 14, 2014|url-status=live}}</ref>\n\nMost experts believed the 1992 team would prevail with a distinct advantage with their centers, [[David Robinson (basketball)|David Robinson]] and [[Patrick Ewing]], over the smaller 2012 team.<ref>{{cite news |last=Turner |first=Broderick |title=Original 1992 Dream Team still the best |date=August 7, 2012 |newspaper=Los Angeles Times |url=https://www.latimes.com/sports/sportsnow/la-sp-sn-dream-team-20120807,0,2437528.story |archiveurl=https://www.webcitation.org/69vNXO6P2?url=http://www.latimes.com/sports/sportsnow/la-sp-sn-dream-team-20120807,0,2437528.story |archivedate=2012-08-15 |url-status=live |access-date=2012-08-15 }}</ref><ref>{{cite news|last=Wilbon |first=Michael |title=Dream Team set bar at Olympics |date=July 26, 2012 |work=ESPN.com |url=http://espn.go.com/los-angeles/story/_/id/8201633/2012-olympics-dream-team-legacy-set-bar-olympic-quality |archiveurl=https://www.webcitation.org/69vMHFFXK?url=http://espn.go.com/los-angeles/story/_/id/8201633/2012-olympics-dream-team-legacy-set-bar-olympic-quality |archivedate=August 15, 2012 |url-status=live }}</ref> Chandler was the only {{convert|7|ft|m|adj=on}} player on the 2012 team, but his offensive game was limited.<ref>{{cite news|last=Price |first=Greg |title=US Wins Gold Over Spain: So Are LeBron, Kobe, And Co. Better Than 1992 Dream Team? |date=August 12, 2012 |newspaper=International Business Times |url=http://www.ibtimes.com/articles/372811/20120812/dream-team-kobe-bryant-lebron-james-michael.htm |archiveurl=https://www.webcitation.org/69wx2jCvn?url=http://www.ibtimes.com/articles/372811/20120812/dream-team-kobe-bryant-lebron-james-michael.htm |archivedate=August 16, 2012 |url-status=live }}</ref> Some felt the discussion might have been more compelling if Dwight Howard and other injured big men were on the 2012 squad.<ref name=stein_magic/><ref>{{cite news|last=Simmons |first=Bill |title=The London Chronicles, Vol. 7: The Olympic Mega-Bag, Part 1 |date=August 13, 2012 |work=grantland.com |publisher=ESPN Internet Ventures |url=http://www.grantland.com/story/_/id/8264283/olympic-mega-bag |archiveurl=https://www.webcitation.org/69vNibJWg?url=http://www.grantland.com/story/_/id/8264283/olympic-mega-bag |archivedate=August 15, 2012 |url-status=live }}</ref><ref>{{cite news|last=Deveney |first=Sean |title=Olympics 2012: Comparing Team USA basketball to 2008 squad |date=July 28, 2012 |work=sportingnews.com |url=http://aol.sportingnews.com/olympics/story/2012-07-28/olympics-2012-team-usa-basketball-past-results-compare-lebron-james-kobe-bryant |archiveurl=https://www.webcitation.org/69vNq9s39?url=http://aol.sportingnews.com/olympics/story/2012-07-28/olympics-2012-team-usa-basketball-past-results-compare-lebron-james-kobe-bryant |archivedate=August 15, 2012 |url-status=live }}</ref> NBA coach [[Doc Rivers]] felt the London team had an advantage with their outside shooting over the Dream Team.<ref name=amick/> Like Barkley, [[CBSSports.com]] opined that only three members of the 2012 team\u2014Bryant, James, and Durant\u2014would have made the Dream Team.<ref>{{cite news|last=Golliver|first=Ben|title=Michael Jordan, Charles Barkley to Kobe Bryant: Dream Team better than 2012 squad|date=July 12, 2012|work=CBSSports.com|url=http://www.cbssports.com/nba/eye-on-basketball/19571318/michael-jordan-charles-barkley-tell-kobe-bryant-dream-team-was-better-than-2012-squad|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20141214081540/http://www.cbssports.com/nba/eye-on-basketball/19571318/michael-jordan-charles-barkley-tell-kobe-bryant-dream-team-was-better-than-2012-squad|archivedate=December 14, 2014|url-status=live}}</ref>\n\nThe Dream Team averaged 117.3 points and won its games by an average of 43.8 points. The 2012 team averaged a similar point total (115.5) but won by a lesser margin (32.1). The Dream Team beat [[Croatia national basketball team|Croatia]] by 32 in the gold-medal game, while the 2012 team won by just seven. However, the level of international competition improved since 1992.<ref name=amick>{{cite news|last=Amick |first=Sam |title=Jordan: Dream Team would have no problem vs. London gold medalists |date=August 15, 2012 |work=SI.com |url=http://sportsillustrated.cnn.com/2012/writers/sam_amick/08/15/michael-jordan/index.html |archiveurl=https://www.webcitation.org/69wxpn5fO?url=http://sportsillustrated.cnn.com/2012/writers/sam_amick/08/15/michael-jordan/index.html |archivedate=August 16, 2012 |url-status=live }}</ref><ref>{{cite news|last=Levin |first=Josh |title=What's the Difference Between the 1992 and 2012 Dream Teams? Kevin Durant and LeBron James Played Tougher Competition. |date=August 12, 2012 |magazine=Slate |url=http://www.slate.com/blogs/five_ring_circus/2012/08/12/_2012_u_s_olympic_basketball_team_the_original_dream_team_was_great_but_lebron_james_and_kevin_durant_played_tougher_competition_.html |archiveurl=https://www.webcitation.org/69wxzZB0e?url=http://www.slate.com/blogs/five_ring_circus/2012/08/12/_2012_u_s_olympic_basketball_team_the_original_dream_team_was_great_but_lebron_james_and_kevin_durant_played_tougher_competition_.html |archivedate=August 16, 2012 |url-status=live }}</ref> The 2012 team faced a tougher opponent in Spain, which had seven NBA players; Croatia in 1992 had only two NBA players at that point.<ref name=diamond/> Overall, the 2012 Olympic field had 39 NBA players and 18 former NBA players were on team rosters, while rosters in 1992 had 17 NBA players and three other former players\u2014more than half of those NBA players were on the Dream Team.<ref>{{cite news\n |last=Zillgitt \n |first=Jeff \n |title=USA men survive Spain to win basketball gold medal \n |date=August 12, 2012 \n |newspaper=USA Today \n |url=https://www.usatoday.com/sports/olympics/london/basketball/story/2012-08-12/usa-gold-medal-game-spain/57009558/1?loc=interstitialskip \n |archiveurl=https://www.webcitation.org/69wcpjwU5?url=http://www.usatoday.com/sports/olympics/london/basketball/story/2012-08-12/usa-gold-medal-game-spain/57009558/1?loc=interstitialskip \n |archivedate=August 15, 2012 \n |url-status=live \n}}</ref>\n\n==Notes==\n{{reflist|group=lower-alpha}}\n\n==References==\n;General\n*{{cite news |title=USA Combined Team Statistics (as of Aug 12, 2012) |work=usabasketball.com |url=http://www.usabasketball.com/misc/12_moly_stats_usa.pdf |archiveurl=https://www.webcitation.org/69tnSJGCi?url=http://www.usabasketball.com/misc/12_moly_stats_usa.pdf |archivedate=August 14, 2012 |url-status=dead |df=mdy-all |access-date=August 14, 2012 }}\n\n;Specific\n{{Reflist|30em}}\n\n==External links==\n{{Commons category|United States men's national basketball team at the 2012 Summer Olympics|2012 United States men's Olympic basketball team}}\n* [https://web.archive.org/web/20140903135856/http://archive.usab.com/mens/national/12_moly_results.html 2012 Men's Olympic Basketball Competition Results] at usabasketball.com\n\n{{United States men's national basketball team}}\n{{United States Men Basketball Squad 2012 Summer Olympics}}\n{{Basketball at the 2012 Summer Olympics \u2013 Men's tournament}}\n{{Summer Olympics basketball tournament winners}}\n\n[[Category:United States at the Olympic Men's Basketball Tournament]]\n[[Category:Countries at the 2012 Olympic Men's Basketball Tournament|United States]]\n[[Category:2012\u201313 in American basketball|Olympics]]\n", "text_old": "{{Infobox basketball club season\n| club               = '''2012 United States men's Olympic basketball team'''\n| season             = '''[[Basketball at the Summer Olympics]]'''\n| image              = \n| image_size         = \n| alt                = \n| caption            =    \n| manager            = [[ Mike Krzyzewski]]\n| stadium            = \n| league             = [[Basketball at the 2012 Summer Olympics \u2013 Men's tournament|2012 Summer Olympics]]\n| league result      = {{Olympic Gold medal}}  \n| PIR_leader         = \n| pir_n              = \n| pir                = \n| top_scorer         = [[Kevin Durant]]\n| ppg_n              = USA\n| ppg                = 19.5\n| rebounds_leader    = [[Kevin Love]]\n| rpg_n              = USA\n| rpg                = 7.6\n| assists_leader     = [[LeBron James]] \n| apg_n              = USA\n| apg                = 5.6\n| highest attendance = \n| lowest attendance  = \n| average attendance = \n| largest win        = \n| largest loss       = \n| h_title            = \n| h_body             = \n| h_pattern_b        = \n| h_shorts           = \n| h_pattern_s        = \n| a_title            = \n| a_body             = \n| a_pattern_b        = \n| a_shorts           = \n| a_pattern_s        = \n| 3_title            = \n| 3_body             = \n| 3_pattern_b        = \n| 3_shorts           = \n| 3_pattern_s        = \n| prevseason         = [[2008 United States men's Olympic basketball team|2008]]\n| nextseason         = [[2016 United States men's Olympic basketball team|2016]]\n}}\n\nThe [[United States men's national basketball team|men's national basketball team]] of the [[United States at the 2012 Summer Olympics|United States]] won the gold medal at the [[Basketball at the 2012 Summer Olympics|2012 Summer Olympics]] in London. Defending the gold medal won by the [[2008 United States men's Olympic basketball team|2008 team]] in the [[Basketball at the 2008 Summer Olympics|previous Olympic Games]], the Americans qualified for the 2012 Games after winning the [[2010 United States men's FIBA World Championship team|2010 FIBA World Championship]]. The Olympic team lost some players to injuries who might have made the team, and appeared to be short on big men. Their roster featured five players returning from the 2008 Olympic team and five others from the 2010 World Championship. Coming off a victory in the 2011-2012 [[National Basketball Association]] (NBA) finals, [[LeBron James]] became the leader of the Olympic team.\n\nThe USA went undefeated but appeared vulnerable in five exhibition games. They finished the tournament with a perfect 8\u20130 record, defeating opponents by an average of 32 [[point (basketball)|point]]s while trailing in the fourth quarter only once. The Americans often played with a [[small lineup]] that emphasized speed, quickness, and outside shooting. The team set an Olympic single-game record with 156 points scored against [[Nigeria national basketball team|Nigeria]] in the preliminary round. In a rematch of the 2008 finals, Team USA again defeated [[Spain national basketball team|Spain]] to capture the gold.\n\n==Roster==\n[[File:Bryant on the ball.jpg|thumb|right|The 2012 team practicing in Washington, D.C.]]\nThe 2012 team consisted of returning [[2008 United States men's Olympic basketball team|2008 Olympic gold medal winners]] small forwards [[LeBron James]] and [[Carmelo Anthony]], point guards [[Chris Paul]] and [[Deron Williams]], and shooting guard [[Kobe Bryant]]. It also featured [[2010 United States men's FIBA World Championship team|2010 World Championship]] winners small forwards [[Kevin Durant]] and [[Andre Iguodala]], power forward [[Kevin Love]], center [[Tyson Chandler]], and point guard [[Russell Westbrook]]. The final two roster spots were claimed by shooting guard [[James Harden]], and power forward [[Blake Griffin]]; they were chosen over shooting guard [[Eric Gordon]], small forward [[Rudy Gay]], and power forward [[Anthony Davis (basketball)|Anthony Davis]].<ref>{{cite news|title=Griffin, Harden, Iguodala on roster |date=July 8, 2012 |work=ESPN.com |agency=Associated Press |url=http://espn.go.com/olympics/summer/2012/basketball/story/_/id/8139144/2012-olympics-blake-griffin-james-harden-andre-iguodala-us-men-basketball-roster |archiveurl=https://www.webcitation.org/68zvumvLB?url=http://espn.go.com/olympics/summer/2012/basketball/story/_/id/8139144/2012-olympics-blake-griffin-james-harden-andre-iguodala-us-men-basketball-roster |archivedate=July 8, 2012 |url-status=live }}</ref> Griffin then sustained a [[torn meniscus]] during practice and was replaced by Davis, the [[List of first overall NBA draft picks|number one overall pick]] of the [[2012 NBA Draft]], who earlier was unable to practice during the final tryouts due to an ankle injury.<ref>{{cite news|last=Zillgitt |first=Jeff |title=Blake Griffin out of Olympics with torn meniscus |date=July 13, 2012 |newspaper=USA Today |url=http://content.usatoday.com/communities/gameon/post/2012/07/blake-griffin-injury-could-return-anthony-davis-to-olympics/1#.T__JlZF0hEI |archiveurl=https://www.webcitation.org/697XlDv7t?url=http://content.usatoday.com/communities/gameon/post/2012/07/blake-griffin-injury-could-return-anthony-davis-to-olympics/1 |archivedate=July 13, 2012 |url-status=live }}</ref> Forward [[Lamar Odom]] removed himself from consideration in July before the start of training camp.<ref>{{cite news|last=Young|first=Royce|title=Lamar Odom off Team USA, nine players guaranteed spots|date=July 2, 2012|work=cbssports.com|url=http://www.cbssports.com/nba/blog/eye-on-basketball/19466174/lamar-odom-off-team-usa-nine-players-guaranteed-spots|accessdate=July 3, 2012}}</ref>\n\nThe initial 20 finalists were announced in January 2012. In addition to Griffin, others withdrew due to injury including power forwards [[Chris Bosh]] (abdomen) and [[LaMarcus Aldridge]] (torn meniscus), point guards [[Derrick Rose]] ([[anterior cruciate ligament injury|ACL]]) and [[Chauncey Billups]], shooting guard [[Dwyane Wade]] (knee), and center [[Dwight Howard]] (back surgery).  Harden and Davis were added as replacements.<ref>{{cite news|url=https://www.usatoday.com/sports/olympics/london/basketball/story/2012-06-29/chris-bosh-to-miss-olympics/55919170/1 |title = Chris Bosh out of Olympics to rest, rehab injury |publisher=usatoday.com |date=June 29, 2012|accessdate=2012-06-29}}</ref><ref>{{cite news|url=https://www.usatoday.com/sports/olympics/london/basketball/story/2012-06-28/dwayne-wade-knee-surgery-miss-olympics/55898344/1 |title=Dwyane Wade to miss Olympics due to knee surgery |publisher=usatoday.com |date= June 28, 2012|accessdate=2012-06-28}}</ref> Center [[Andrew Bynum]] declined an invitation to be added as a finalist.<ref>{{cite news|last=Bresnahan |first=Mike |title=Andrew Bynum says he'll skip Olympics |date=April 20, 2012 |newspaper=Los Angeles Times |url=https://articles.latimes.com/2012/apr/20/sports/la-sp-lakers-fyi-20120421 |archiveurl=https://www.webcitation.org/68zw7LTzn?url=http://articles.latimes.com/2012/apr/20/sports/la-sp-lakers-fyi-20120421 |archivedate=July 8, 2012 |url-status=live }}</ref>\n\nThe final team was built on quickness and speed.<ref>{{cite news|last=Gregory |first=Sean |title=How Team USA Won Men\u2019s Hoops \u2014 and the Entire Olympics |date=August 12, 2012 |work=time.com |url=http://olympics.time.com/2012/08/12/how-team-usa-won-mens-hoops-and-the-entire-olympics/ |archiveurl=https://www.webcitation.org/69vOmLiaK?url=http://olympics.time.com/2012/08/12/how-team-usa-won-mens-hoops-and-the-entire-olympics/ |archivedate=August 15, 2012 |url-status=live }}</ref> While the roster appeared to be weakened by the injuries to its inside players, Team USA executive director [[Jerry Colangelo]] believed the team was deeper, more athletic and more experienced than the 2008 gold-medal team.<ref name=bishop>{{cite news|last=Bishop |first=Greg |title=An Opening Statement Punctuated by Dunks |date=July 29, 2012 |newspaper=The New York Times |url=https://www.nytimes.com/2012/07/30/sports/olympics/in-first-test-us-mens-basketball-team-makes-winning-look-easy.html?_r=1 |archiveurl=https://www.webcitation.org/69Y1GrVIY?url=http://www.nytimes.com/2012/07/30/sports/olympics/in-first-test-us-mens-basketball-team-makes-winning-look-easy.html?_r=2 |archivedate=July 30, 2012 |url-status=live }}</ref>\n\n{{2012 Summer Olympics United States men's basketball team roster}}\n\n==Exhibition games==\nThe United States went undefeated at 5\u20130 in their exhibition games, but were behind early against Brazil and Spain and played a close game against Argentina.<ref name=stein_spain/>\n\n{{Basketballbox\n| bg         = #eee\n| date       = July 12, 2012\n| time       = \n| teamA      = '''United States {{flagdeco|USA}}'''\n| scoreA     = '''113'''\n| scoreB     = 59\n| Q1         = '''26'''\u201312\n| Q2         = '''24'''\u201315\n| Q3         = '''29'''\u201314\n| Q4         = '''34'''\u201318\n| report     = [https://web.archive.org/web/20140714163417/http://www.usab.com/misc/12_mnt_exh_game_01_box.pdf Report]\n| teamB      = {{bk|Dominican Republic}}\n| points1    = [[Kevin Durant|Durant]] 24\n| rebounds1  = [[Kevin Durant|Durant]] 10\n| assist1    = [[Deron Williams|Williams]] 10\n| otherstat1 = \n| points2    = [[Elipidio Fortuna|Fortuna]] 10\n| rebounds2  = [[Jack Martinez|Martinez]] 9\n| assist2    = [[Al Horford|Horford]] 3\n| otherstat2 = \n| place      = [[Thomas and Mack Center]], [[Paradise, Nevada|Paradise]], [[Nevada]], [[United States|USA]]\n| attendance = \n| referee    = Jos\u00e9 Carrion, Bill Kennedy, Scott Bolnick\n| TV         = \n}}\n{{Basketballbox\n| bg         = #fff\n| date       = July 16, 2012\n| time       = \n| teamA      = '''United States {{flagdeco|USA}}'''\n| scoreA     = '''80'''\n| scoreB     = 69\n| Q1         = 17\u2013'''27'''\n| Q2         = '''20'''\u20135\n| Q3         = '''22'''\u201319\n| Q4         = '''21'''\u201318\n| report     = [https://web.archive.org/web/20130202215526/http://www.usabasketball.com/misc/12_mnt_exh_02_box.pdf Report]\n| teamB      = {{bk|Brazil}}\n| points1    = [[LeBron James|James]] 30\n| rebounds1  = [[LeBron James|James]] 6\n| assist1    = [[Chris Paul|Paul]] 3\n| otherstat1 = \n| points2    = [[Alex Garcia (basketball)|Garcia]] 14\n| rebounds2  = [[Anderson Varej\u00e3o|Varej\u00e3o]] 13\n| assist2    = [[Marcelinho Huertas|Huertas]] 3\n| otherstat2 = \n| place      = [[Capital One Arena|Verizon Center]], [[Washington, D.C.]], [[United States|USA]]\n| attendance = \n| referee    = \n| TV         = \n}}\n{{Basketballbox\n| bg         = #eee\n| date       = July 18, 2012\n| time       = \n| teamA      = '''United States {{flagdeco|USA}}'''\n| scoreA     = '''118'''\n| scoreB     = 78\n| Q1         = '''33'''\u201320\n| Q2         = '''22'''\u201317\n| Q3         = '''34'''\u201318\n| Q4         = '''29'''\u201323\n| report     = [https://web.archive.org/web/20120815112227/http://www.usabasketball.com/misc/12_mnt_exh_03_box.pdf Report]\n| teamB      = {{bk|Great Britain}}\n| points1    = [[Carmelo Anthony|Anthony]], [[Deron Williams|Williams]] 21\n| rebounds1  = [[Andre Iguodala|Iguodala]], [[LeBron James|James]] 6\n| assist1    = [[Russell Westbrook|Westbrook]] 9\n| otherstat1 = \n| points2    = [[Luol Deng|Deng]] 25\n| rebounds