ertain, Marat Kogut, Oscvar Lorente\n| TV         = \n}}\n\n==Olympic play==\n{{Further|Basketball at the 2012 Summer Olympics \u2013 Men}}\n[[File:LeBron James 2012 USA team.jpg|thumb|upright|270px|[[LeBron James]] assumed leadership of Team USA in 2012.]]\nThe Americans went an undefeated 8\u20130 and averaged 116 points per game, winning by an average margin of 32.1 points\u2014the fifth highest in US Olympic history.<ref name=diamond>{{cite news|last=Diamond |first=Jared |title=The Fifth-Best Basketball Team of All Time |date=August 12, 2012 |newspaper=The Wall Street Journal |url=https://www.wsj.com/articles/SB10000872396390444184704577585242901176220?mod=wsj_streaming_stream |archiveurl=https://www.webcitation.org/69vCVh0C0?url=http://online.wsj.com/article/SB10000872396390444184704577585242901176220.html?mod=wsj_streaming_stream |archivedate=August 14, 2012 |url-status=live }}</ref><ref name=stein_spain_ia/> Team USA trailed in the fourth quarter only once, against [[Lithuania men's national basketball team|Lithuania]] in the opening round.<ref>{{cite news|last=Isola |first=Frank |title=LeBron James and Team USA win gold at London Olympics  with 100\u2013107 win over Spain; Kevin Durant scores 30 |date=August 12, 2012 |newspaper=New York Daily News |url=http://www.nydailynews.com/sports/olympics-2012/lebron-james-team-usa-win-gold-london-olympics-100-107-win-spain-kevin-durant-scores-30-article-1.1134783 |archiveurl=https://www.webcitation.org/69wofxe8P?url=http://www.nydailynews.com/sports/olympics-2012/lebron-james-team-usa-win-gold-london-olympics-100-107-win-spain-kevin-durant-scores-30-article-1.1134783 |archivedate=August 16, 2012 |url-status=live }}</ref> James became the leader of the team with Bryant\u2014who would turn 34 in August 2012\u2014stepping back.<ref name=ap_column>{{cite news|title=Column: Going out in style \u2013 'K Boys' golden again |date=August 12, 2012 |work=ESPN.com |agency=Associated Press |url=http://sports.espn.go.com/espn/wire?section=oly&id=8262281 |archiveurl=https://www.webcitation.org/69tfnB8jj?url=http://sports.espn.go.com/espn/wire?section=oly&id=8262281 |archivedate=August 13, 2012 |url-status=live }}</ref><ref>{{cite news |last=Medina |first=Mark |title=Kobe Bryant ends Olympic career on a high note |date=August 12, 2012 |newspaper=Los Angeles Times |url=https://www.latimes.com/sports/lakersnow/la-sp-ln-la-london-olympics-kobe-bryant-ends-olympic-career-on-a-high-note-20120813,0,6931992.story |archiveurl=https://www.webcitation.org/69tg5zH1W?url=http://www.latimes.com/sports/lakersnow/la-sp-ln-la-london-olympics-kobe-bryant-ends-olympic-career-on-a-high-note-20120813,0,6931992.story |archivedate=2012-08-13 |url-status=live |access-date=2012-08-14 }}</ref><ref>{{cite news |last=Medina |first=Mark |title=London Olympics: 5 things to take from Team USA's win over Spain |date=August 12, 2012 |newspaper=Los Angeles Times |url=https://www.latimes.com/sports/lakersnow/la-sp-ln-la-london-olympics-5-things-to-take-from-team-usas-win-over-spain-20120812,0,6456027.story |archiveurl=https://www.webcitation.org/69tgFXNJH?url=http://www.latimes.com/sports/lakersnow/la-sp-ln-la-london-olympics-5-things-to-take-from-team-usas-win-over-spain-20120812,0,6456027.story |archivedate=2012-08-13 |url-status=live |access-date=2012-08-14 }}</ref> James facilitated the offense from the post and perimeter, called the defensive sets, and provided scoring when needed.<ref name=freeman>{{cite news|last=Freeman |first=Eric |title=The Team USA Reputations Index: How the gold medal changes our opinions of these players |date=August 13, 2012 |work=yahoo.com |url=https://sports.yahoo.com/blogs/nba-ball-dont-lie/team-usa-reputations-index-gold-medal-changes-opinions-140024134--nba.html |archiveurl=https://www.webcitation.org/69tklmjoF?url=http://sports.yahoo.com/blogs/nba-ball-dont-lie/team-usa-reputations-index-gold-medal-changes-opinions-140024134--nba.html |archivedate=August 13, 2012 |url-status=live }}</ref><ref name=cacciola>{{cite news|last=Cacciola |first=Scott |title=Summer of LeBron Ends With Gold |date=August 12, 2012 |newspaper=The Wall Street Journal |url=https://www.wsj.com/articles/SB10000872396390444318104577585193378735380 |archiveurl=https://www.webcitation.org/69vBbpXYR?url=http://online.wsj.com/article/SB10000872396390444318104577585193378735380.html |archivedate=August 14, 2012 |url-status=live }}</ref><ref name=bishop_nigeria/><ref>{{cite news|last=Stein |first=Marc |title=Once again, LeBron answers the call |date=August 8, 2012 |work=ESPN.com |url=http://espn.go.com/olympics/summer/2012/basketball/story/_/id/8249604/2012-olympics-once-again-lebron-james-answers-call |archiveurl=https://www.webcitation.org/69vE85m5W?url=http://espn.go.com/olympics/summer/2012/basketball/story/_/id/8249604/2012-olympics-once-again-lebron-james-answers-call |archivedate=August 14, 2012 |url-status=live }}</ref> After winning the gold, Team USA coach [[Mike Krzyzewski]] said James \"is the best player, he is the best leader and he is as smart as anybody playing the game right now\".<ref>{{cite news|last=Deveney |first=Sean |title=Olympics 2012: The golden era of LeBron James |date=August 12, 2012 |work=SportingNews.com |url=http://aol.sportingnews.com/olympics/story/2012-08-12/olympics-2012-lebron-james-team-usa-spain-carmelo-anthony-london-games-us-gold-m |archiveurl=https://www.webcitation.org/69thGegfJ?url=http://aol.sportingnews.com/olympics/story/2012-08-12/olympics-2012-lebron-james-team-usa-spain-carmelo-anthony-london-games-us-gold-m |archivedate=August 13, 2012 |url-status=live }}</ref> Durant scored a United States Olympics record of 156 points in the tournament.<ref name=bishop_spain>{{cite news |last=Bishop |first=Greg |title=James and U.S. Replenish Gold in Treasure Chest |date=August 12, 2012 |newspaper=The New York Times |url=https://www.nytimes.com/2012/08/13/sports/olympics/lebron-james-and-united-states-win-gold-in-mens-basketball.html?_r=1&ref=sports |archiveurl=https://www.webcitation.org/69thmknIG?url=http://www.nytimes.com/2012/08/13/sports/olympics/lebron-james-and-united-states-win-gold-in-mens-basketball.html?_r=2&ref=sports |archivedate=2012-08-13 |url-status=live |access-date=2017-02-26 }}</ref> He also made 34 [[three-point field goals]], doubling the previous United States mark of 17; Anthony (23) also exceed the old record.<ref name=stein_spain_ia/> Bryant was not in peak condition early, but he played himself into shape and was a key contributor in the final three games.<ref name=ap_column/> While Chandler was the team's only true center\u2014Davis was thin and had no professional experience\u2014Krzyzewski also played Love, James or Anthony as Team USA's de facto center.<ref name=freeman/><ref>{{cite news|last=Dwyer |first=Kelly |title=Behind the Box Score, where Kobe Bryant went off, and the Aussies went down |date=August 8, 2012 |work=yahoo.com |url=https://sports.yahoo.com/blogs/olympics-fourth-place-medal/behind-box-score-where-kobe-bryant-went-off-000137104--oly.html |archiveurl=https://www.webcitation.org/69tmqCy66?url=http://sports.yahoo.com/blogs/olympics-fourth-place-medal/behind-box-score-where-kobe-bryant-went-off-000137104--oly.html |archivedate=August 14, 2012 |url-status=live }}</ref><ref>{{cite news|last=Haberstroh|first=Tom|title=Kevin Love deserves some ... love|date=August 8, 2012|work=ESPN.com|url=http://insider.espn.go.com/olympics/basketball/story/_/id/8249487/olympics-once-questioned-kevin-love-doing-dirty-work-team-usa|accessdate=August 13, 2012|quote=When Blake Griffin, Chris Bosh and Dwight Howard got scratched for the Olympics squad, a pocket of Americans worried about the prospects of having no real backup center on Team USA. It was Tyson Chandler and ... Love.}}{{subscription required}}</ref> Love led the team with 61 [[rebound (basketball)|rebound]]s (27 offensive).<ref name=freeman/>\n\nCompensating for its lack of big men, the USA played [[small ball (basketball)|small ball]] and spread its playmakers around the three-point line and with a player penetrating and passing the ball back outside.<ref name=bishop_spain/> They won with \"basically five players on the perimeter,\" Spain coach [[Sergio Scariolo]] said.<ref name=stein_spain/> Bryant and Krzyzewski declared at the completion of the tournament that 2012 was their final Olympic appearance. They both joined Team USA after the disappointing bronze finish in the [[Basketball at the 2004 Summer Olympics|2004 Games]].<ref name=ap_column/> Krzyzewski left with a 62\u20131 record and a 50-game winning streak in international play for the Americans.<ref name=stein_spain_ia/> He joined [[Henry Iba]] as the only US coaches to lead the team to consecutive Olympic gold medals.<ref name=cacciola/> In 2013, Team USA announced Krzyzewski would return as head coach from 2013 through 2016.<ref>{{cite web|title=2013 USA Basketball Men\u2019s National Team Mini-Camp |page=6 |publisher=USA Basketball |url=http://www.usab.com/misc/13_mnt_Mini_Camp_guide.pdf |archiveurl=https://www.webcitation.org/6QL8BZ3Zz?url=http://www.usab.com/misc/13_mnt_Mini_Camp_guide.pdf |archivedate=June 15, 2014 |url-status=dead |df= }}</ref>\n\n===Preliminary round===\nThe USA competed in Group A in the opening round. Teams played in a [[round-robin tournament|round robin]] format with the top four teams advancing to the next round. The Americans ended group play 5\u20130, the only undefeated team and the group's top seed.<ref name=stein_argentina/>\n\n{{2012 Summer Olympics men's basketball group A standings}}\n\n====France====\n{{2012 Summer Olympics men's basketball game A2|bgc=#eeeeee|df=mdy}}\nDurant scored 22 points, and James had eight [[assist (basketball)|assist]]s while taking only six shots as the USA won their opening game 98\u201371 over [[France national basketball team|France]].<ref name=bishop/> The USA was never in any real trouble, but played sloppy in the beginning, missing their first six three-point attempts and being called for 18 personal fouls in the first half. Anthony and Westbrook spent the final six minutes of the half on the bench after their third personal fouls. The team led 52\u201336 at halftime, which expanded to 78\u201351 after three quarters. Krzyzewski was able to rest Bryant, James, and Durant for most of the final period, and even the 19-year-old Davis played.<ref name=ap_france>{{cite news|title=U.S. drains 3s to pull away |date=July 29, 2012 |work=ESPN.com |agency=Associated Press |url=http://espn.go.com/olympics/summer/2012/basketball/story/_/id/8211257/2012-summer-olympics-kevin-durant-us-drain-3s-pull-away-france |archiveurl=https://www.webcitation.org/69Wk3rFMI?url=http://espn.go.com/olympics/summer/2012/basketball/story/_/id/8211257/2012-summer-olympics-kevin-durant-us-drain-3s-pull-away-france |archivedate=July 29, 2012 |url-status=live }}</ref>\n\nDurant, Anthony, and Chandler contributed nine rebounds each, and Love finished with 14 points.  Bryant, James and Durant finished the game a combined 6 for 12 on three-pointers, while the rest of the team shot 2 for 13. France's team featured six NBA players, including [[Tony Parker]].<ref name=ap_france/>\n\n====Tunisia====\n{{2012 Summer Olympics men's basketball game A6|bgc=#eeeeee|df=mdy}}\nThe USA won in a 110\u201363 blowout over [[Tunisia national basketball team|Tunisia]], but only after Krzyzewski benched his starters\u2014Bryant, James, Durant, Paul, and Chandler\u2014to begin the second half. The reserves\u2014Love, Anthony, Iguodala, Williams and Westbrook\u2014responded with a 21\u20133 run to open the half, turning a 46\u201333 halftime lead to a 67\u201336 advantage.<ref name=ap_tunisia>{{cite news|title=Team USA blows out Tunisia |date=July 31, 2012 |work=ESPN.com |agency=Associated Press |url=http://espn.go.com/olympics/summer/2012/basketball/story/_/id/8220094/2012-summer-olympics-carmelo-anthony-kevin-love-lead-team-usa-rout-tunisia |archiveurl=https://www.webcitation.org/69a0k8CzB?url=http://espn.go.com/olympics/summer/2012/basketball/story/_/id/8220094/2012-summer-olympics-carmelo-anthony-kevin-love-lead-team-usa-rout-tunisia |archivedate=August 1, 2012 |url-status=live }}</ref><ref name=stein_tunisia>{{cite news|last=Stein |first=Mark |title=Instant Analysis: Team USA 110, Tunisia 63 |date=July 31, 2012 |work=ESPN.com |url=http://sports.espn.go.com/blog/olympics/post/_/id/3106/instant-analysis-team-usa-110-tunisia-63 |archiveurl=https://www.webcitation.org/69a1Bo8ry?url=http://sports.espn.go.com/blog/olympics/post/_/id/3106/instant-analysis-team-usa-110-tunisia-63 |archivedate=August 1, 2012 |url-status=live }}</ref> Tunisia, the consensus weakest team in the Olympics and listed by one website as 54-point underdogs, led the game 15\u201312 after nine minutes, and trailed only 35\u201330 with about {{fract|3|1|2}} minutes remaining in the first half.  The Americans then scored 11 consecutive points.<ref name=ap_tunisia/><ref name=stein_tunisia/>\n\nLike the opening game when they missed their first six three-pointers, the USA started this game an even worse 0-for-8.<ref name=ap_tunisia/> Colangelo said opponents' strategy was to force the Americans to shoot from outside and hope for an off night. The USA made 17 of 22 on conventional field goals in the first half, while missing 10 of 12 from three-point range. This was the team's second consecutive slow start in the Olympics, following the pattern in their five earlier exhibition games.<ref name=bishop_tunisia>{{cite news|last=Bishop |first=Greg |title=Slow Start, but U.S. Men\u2019s Basketball Team More Than Makes Up for It in a Rout |date=July 31, 2012 |newspaper=The New York Times |url=https://www.nytimes.com/2012/08/01/sports/olympics/us-mens-olympic-basketball-team-recovers-from-slow-start-to-rout-tunisia.html?_r=1 |archiveurl=https://www.webcitation.org/69bK2E5HH?url=http://www.nytimes.com/2012/08/01/sports/olympics/us-mens-olympic-basketball-team-recovers-from-slow-start-to-rout-tunisia.html?_r=2 |archivedate=August 1, 2012 |url-status=live }}</ref> The Americans scored on a variety of dunks once the game was in hand. Anthony and Love led the team with 16 points. Six Americans scored in double figures, including Durant who had 13 points and added 10 rebounds and 5 assists.<ref name=ap_tunisia/><ref name=bishop_tunisia/>\n\n====Nigeria====\n{{2012 Summer Olympics men's basketball game A9|bgc=#eeeeee|df=mdy}}\nThe USA answered critics of their slow starts and outside shooting with a 156\u201373 blowout of [[Nigeria national basketball team|Nigeria]]. The Americans scored an Olympic-record 78 points in the first half en route to breaking the record for points in a game of 138, set by [[Brazil men's national basketball team|Brazil]] against [[Egypt men's national basketball team|Egypt]] in [[Basketball at the 1988 Summer Olympics|1988]]. The record was broken with 4:37 left to play, and the team set USA records for 3-pointers (29), field goals (59), field goal percentage (71%), and margin of victory (83).<ref name=ap_nigeria>{{cite news|title=U.S. men break points record with 156 |date=August 2, 2012 |work=ESPN.com |agency=Associated Press |url=http://espn.go.com/olympics/summer/2012/basketball/story/_/id/8227877/2012-summer-olympics-us-men-hoops-scores-156-shatter-olympics-points-record |archiveurl=https://www.webcitation.org/69dHbzreG?url=http://espn.go.com/olympics/summer/2012/basketball/story/_/id/8227877/2012-summer-olympics-us-men-hoops-scores-156-shatter-olympics-points-record |archivedate=August 3, 2012 |url-status=live }}</ref>\n\nAnthony scored 37 points in only 14 minutes of play, shooting 10 of 12 on three-pointers and breaking the USA single-game scoring record in less than three quarters.<ref name=ap_nigeria/><ref name=stein_magic/> He broke [[Stephon Marbury]]'s record of 31 against [[Spain men's national basketball team|Spain]] in [[Basketball at the 2004 Summer Olympics \u2013 Men|2004]]. Bryant scored 16 points, 14 in the first quarter, as the USA scored 49 points in the opening period.  They led 78\u201345 at halftime before doubling their scoring total in the second half. The Americans shot 29 of 46 on three-point attempts (63 percent).<ref name=ap_nigeria/> They more than doubled their previous record of 13 made, which was broken by halftime after 11 three-pointers in the first quarter alone.<ref name=stein_nigeria>{{cite news|last=Stein |first=Marc |title=Nothing but buckets |date=August 2, 2012 |work=ESPN.com |url=http://espn.go.com/olympics/summer/2012/basketball/story/_/id/8228344/2012-olympics-melo-leads-record-setting-team-usa-barrage |archiveurl=https://www.webcitation.org/69dI4AEEB?url=http://espn.go.com/olympics/summer/2012/basketball/story/_/id/8228344/2012-olympics-melo-leads-record-setting-team-usa-barrage |archivedate=August 3, 2012 |url-status=live }}</ref> Krzyzewski defended the blowout, noting that he removed his stars in the second half, ordered a zone defense, and stopped allowing [[fast break]]s in the opening period.<ref name=bishop_blog_08042012>{{cite news|last=Bishop |first=Greg |title=In a Close Game, the United States Beats Lithuania |date=August 4, 2012 |newspaper=The New York Times |url=http://london2012.blogs.nytimes.com/2012/08/04/in-a-close-match-the-unites-states-beats-lithuania-99-94/ |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20120806223703/http://london2012.blogs.nytimes.com/2012/08/04/in-a-close-match-the-unites-states-beats-lithuania-99-94/ |archivedate=August 6, 2012 |url-status=live }}</ref>\n\n====Lithuania====\n{{2012 Summer Olympics men's basketball game A11|bgc=#eeeeee|df=mdy}}\nMainly a facilitator in the first three games,<ref name=bishop_nigeria>{{cite news |last=Bishop |first=Greg |title=LeBron James Is Content With Dishing Off During U.S. Feast |date=August 2, 2012 |newspaper=The New York Times |url=https://www.nytimes.com/2012/08/03/sports/olympics/lebron-james-prefers-to-assist-in-us-teams-victories.html?partner=rss&emc=rss |archiveurl=https://www.webcitation.org/69faDjwFj?url=http://www.nytimes.com/2012/08/03/sports/olympics/lebron-james-prefers-to-assist-in-us-teams-victories.html?_r=1&partner=rss&emc=rss |archivedate=2012-08-04 |url-status=live |access-date=2017-02-26 }}</ref> James scored 9 of his 20 points in the final four minutes as the USA came back to defeat Lithuania 99\u201394.  [[Linas Kleiza]] scored 25 to lead Lithuania, which led by 84\u201382 with 5:50 remaining. The US took a three-point lead, but Lithuania pulled within 87\u201386 with 4:12 in the game. James followed with a three-pointer and a dunk.<ref name=ap_lithuania>{{cite news|title=U.S. men struggle vs. Lithuania |date=August 4, 2012 |agency=Associated Press |work=ESPN.com |url=http://espn.go.com/olympics/summer/2012/basketball/story/_/id/8233394/2012-london-olympics-lebron-james-late-rally-puts-us-men-lithuania |archiveurl=https://www.webcitation.org/69imgP48d?url=http://espn.go.com/olympics/summer/2012/basketball/story/_/id/8233394/2012-london-olympics-lebron-james-late-rally-puts-us-men-lithuania |archivedate=August 6, 2012 |url-status=live }}</ref> Entering the contest, James was averaging just 6.7 points but with 5.7 assists.<ref name=bishop_nigeria/><ref>{{cite news|last=Bishop |first=Greg |title=After Three Routs, a Late Escape |date=August 4, 2012 |newspaper=The New York Times |url=https://www.nytimes.com/2012/08/05/sports/olympics/usa-basketball-routs-despite-scare-vs-lithuania-show-formats-flaws.html?_r=1 |archiveurl=https://www.webcitation.org/69inMPgzK?url=http://www.nytimes.com/2012/08/05/sports/olympics/usa-basketball-routs-despite-scare-vs-lithuania-show-formats-flaws.html?_r=2 |archivedate=August 6, 2012 |url-status=live }}</ref>\n\nAnthony added 20 points, and Paul contributed seven rebounds, six assists and four of the Americans' 17 [[steal (basketball)|steal]]s. The USA made only 10 of 33 attempts on three-point attempts and too often settled for outside shots. Lithuania outrebounded the USA 42\u201337 and shot an impressive 58 percent from the field. The Americans struggled to defend Lithuania's high [[pick-and-roll]]. However, the USA team's deep bench wore Lithuania down in the final period, forcing several [[turnover (basketball)|turnover]]s to determine the outcome in the final minutes.<ref name=ap_lithuania/> Winning their first three games by an average of 52.2 points and playing so well, the team had canceled their previous two practices and rested while watching other sports instead.<ref name=bishop_blog_08042012/>\n\n====Argentina====\n{{2012 Summer Olympics men's basketball game A15|bgc=#eeeeee|df=mdy}}\nDurant scored 17 of his 28 points in the third quarter as the USA turned a one-point game into a 126\u201397 blowout over [[Argentina national basketball team|Argentina]]. The USA led just 60\u201359 at halftime, when Durant matched Argentina's point total during a 42-point third quarter explosion by the Americans. James scored the first seven in the quarter before Durant took over and shot 5 of 6 from three-point range.  He finished 8 of 10 from three-point range, and the team was 20 of 39. James had 18 points in the game, and Paul added 17.<ref name=ap_argentina>{{cite news|title=Team USA rolls by Argentina |date=August 6, 2012 |work=ESPN.com |agency=Associated Press |url=http://espn.go.com/olympics/summer/2012/basketball/story/_/id/8241408/2012-london-olympics-team-usa-pulls-away-argentina |archiveurl=https://www.webcitation.org/69j8wnyYB?url=http://espn.go.com/olympics/summer/2012/basketball/story/_/id/8241408/2012-london-olympics-team-usa-pulls-away-argentina |archivedate=August 7, 2012 |url-status=live }}</ref>\n\nThe USA allowed Argentina to make 11 of its first 15 shots, and the Americans lead was never bigger than six in the second quarter.<ref name=ap_argentina/> Argentina's [[Luis Scola]] did not play in the second period, and starting point guard [[Pablo Prigioni]] sat the entire game. They rested their starters in the fourth quarter in preparation for their quarterfinal meeting against Brazil, and a possible rematch against the Americans in the semifinals. [[Manu Gin\u00f3bili]] led the Argentines with 16 points, all in the first half. The USA finished the first round as the top seed in their group and the only team undefeated in group play.<ref name=stein_argentina>{{cite news|last=Stein |first=Marc |title=Instant Analysis: Team USA 126, Argentina 97 |date=August 6, 2012 |work=ESPN.com |url=http://proxy.espn.go.com/blog/olympics/post/_/id/3330/instant-analysis-team-usa-126-argentina-97 |archiveurl=https://www.webcitation.org/69j98qBYr?url=http://proxy.espn.go.com/blog/olympics/post/_/id/3330/instant-analysis-team-usa-126-argentina-97 |archivedate=August 7, 2012 |url-status=live }}</ref> An American loss by at least 13 points would have placed Argentina instead into the top spot from Group A.<ref name=stein_argentina/><ref name=ap_argentina/>\n\n===Knockout round===\nThe [[single-elimination]] round features the top four teams from each of the two groups from the opening round.\n\n====Quarterfinal \u2013 Australia====\n{{2012 Summer Olympics men's basketball game C4|bgc=#eeeeee|df=mdy}}\nBryant made six straight three-pointers in the second half and James finished with the first [[triple-double]] in USA Olympic history.{{#tag:ref|Assists were recorded as an official statistic starting in 1976.<ref name=triple_double>{{cite web |title=LeBron James Tallies First Triple-Double In U.S. Olympic History To Power USA To Semifinals With 119\u201386 Win Against Australia |date=August 8, 2012 |work=usabasketball.com |url=http://www.usabasketball.com/mens/national/12_moly_game_06.html |archiveurl=https://www.webcitation.org/69vDFCmyl?url=http://www.usabasketball.com/mens/national/12_moly_game_06.html |archivedate=2012-08-14 |url-status=dead |df= |access-date=2012-08-14 }}</ref>|group=lower-alpha}} The Americans surrendered 11 consecutive points to start the second half. The USA was leading by six when Bryant, who shot 0 for 3 in the first half, made consecutive threes to give his team a 70\u201358 lead.<ref name=ap_aus>{{cite news|title=U.S. rolls to basketball semifinals |date=August 8, 2012 |work=ESPN.com |agency=Associated Press |url=http://espn.go.com/olympics/summer/2012/basketball/story/_/id/8249236/2012-summer-olympics-kobe-bryant-lebron-james-lead-us-romp-australia |archiveurl=https://www.webcitation.org/69mCTzBgc?url=http://espn.go.com/olympics/summer/2012/basketball/story/_/id/8249236/2012-summer-olympics-kobe-bryant-lebron-james-lead-us-romp-australia |archivedate=August 9, 2012 |url-status=live }}</ref> He scored all of his 20 points in the second half, including four consecutive three-pointers in a 66-second span.<ref name=stein_aus>{{cite news|last=Stein |first=Marc |title=Instant Analysis: USA 119, Australia 86 |date=August 8, 2012 |work=ESPN.com |url=http://espn.go.com/blog/olympics/post/_/id/3403/instant-analysis-usa-119-australia-86 |archiveurl=https://www.webcitation.org/69mCcpnfF?url=http://espn.go.com/blog/olympics/post/_/id/3403/instant-analysis-usa-119-australia-86 |archivedate=August 9, 2012 |url-status=live }}</ref> He entered the game averaging only 9.4 points.<ref name=ap_aus/>\n\nJames finished with 11 points, 14 rebounds and 11 assists, and he almost had a triple-double by halftime (seven points, 10 rebounds, and six assists).<ref name=stein_aus/> Love added 10 points and 11 rebounds (eight offensive), Anthony scored 17, and Durant had 14.<ref name=ap_aus/><ref name=stein_aus/>\n\n====Semifinal \u2013 Argentina====\n{{2012 Summer Olympics men's basketball game D2|bgc=#eeeeee|df=mdy}}\nThe USA met Argentina for the third time in a span of 17 days in the third straight Olympic semifinal meeting between the two countries.<ref name=ap_aus/><ref name=stein_aus/> Argentina in [[Basketball at the 2004 Summer Olympics \u2013 Men|2004]] was the last team to beat the Americans in Olympic play.<ref name=stein_aus/>\n\nDurant scored 19 points, while James and Anthony added 18 each as the USA pulled away from Argentina in the second half for a 109\u201383 win. Gin\u00f3bili hit a three-pointer at the buzzer at the end of the first half to bring Argentina within 47\u201340, and he scored another three to open the second half to cut the lead to four points.<ref name=ap_semi>{{cite news|title=Kevin Durant, U.S. hit 18 3-pointers, roll into gold-medal game |date=August 10, 2012 |work=ESPN.com |agency=Associated Press |url=http://scores.espn.go.com/olympics/recap?gameId=1168 |archiveurl=https://www.webcitation.org/69pEOlwNW?url=http://scores.espn.go.com/olympics/recap?gameId=1168 |archivedate=August 11, 2012 |url-status=live }}</ref> Durant and James took over the game as the Americans led by 17 points to start the fourth.<ref name=ap_semi/><ref name=stein_semi>{{cite news|last=Stein |first=Marc |title=Instant Analysis: USA 109, Argentina 83 |date=August 10, 2012 |work=ESPN.com |url=http://espn.go.com/blog/olympics/post/_/id/3438/instant-analysis-usa-109-argentina-83 |archiveurl=https://www.webcitation.org/69pEbwEf8?url=http://espn.go.com/blog/olympics/post/_/id/3438/instant-analysis-usa-109-argentina-83 |archivedate=August 11, 2012 |url-status=live }}</ref>\n\nBryant scored 13 points in the first half\u2014including 11 in the first quarter\u2014and Durant made four three-pointers in the third, while Anthony made four of his own in the fourth.<ref name=ap_column/><ref name=stein_semi/> The USA made 18 three-pointers in the game.<ref name=ap_semi/> James finished the game  with seven rebounds and seven assists.<ref name=stein_semi/>\n\n====Final \u2013 Spain====\n{{2012 Summer Olympics men's basketball game E2|bgc=#ffffd0|df=mdy}}\nThe USA met [[Spain national basketball team|Spain]] in the gold medal game, a rematch of the finals in the [[Basketball at the 2008 Summer Olympics \u2013 Men's tournament|2008 Olympics]]. The Americans had won 118\u2013107 in Beijing that year after leading by just four with about {{fract|2|1|2}} minutes left. Spain in 2012 was ranked second in the world behind the US, and had a size advantage with brothers [[Pau Gasol|Pau]] and [[Marc Gasol]].<ref name=cacciola/><ref name=ap_semi/> The Spanish lost games to [[Russia national basketball team|Russia]] and [[Brazil national basketball team|Brazil]] in group play and trailed the Russians by 13 points early in their semifinal win.<ref name=ap_semi/> The USA had also beaten Spain for Olympic gold in [[Basketball at the 1984 Summer Olympics|1984]]. The Americans were 8\u20131 against Spain since the introduction of the NBA players into [[FIBA]] events in 1992.<ref name=stein_semi/>\n\nThe Olympics' own daily preview of the 2012 rematch said it would \"likely take a great game from Spain and an off-day from the USA to cause an upset\".<ref name=ap_spain>{{cite news|title=Kevin Durant, U.S. pull through in final as Spain can't rain on parade |date=August 12, 2012 |work=ESPN.com |agency=Associated Press |url=http://scores.espn.go.com/olympics/summer/2012/basketball/men/recap?gameId=1172 |archiveurl=https://www.webcitation.org/69sAj0PXL?url=http://scores.espn.go.com/olympics/summer/2012/basketball/men/recap?gameId=1172 |archivedate=August 12, 2012 |url-status=live }}</ref> The Americans had been tested only once against Lithuania, and they had dominated opponents in points off turnovers (198\u201377) and fast-break points (175\u201355).<ref>{{cite news|title=U.S. men's basketball team wins gold, beats Spain 107\u2013100 |date=August 12, 2012 |work=CBSSports.com |agency=Associated Press |url=http://www.cbsnews.com/8301-33747_162-57491664/u.s-mens-basketball-team-wins-gold-beats-spain-107-100/ |archiveurl=https://www.webcitation.org/69wpEOz75?url=http://www.cbsnews.com/8301-33747_162-57491664/u.s-mens-basketball-team-wins-gold-beats-spain-107-100/ |archivedate=August 16, 2012 |url-status=live }}</ref> In a game that was close until the final minutes, the USA defeated Spain 107\u2013100. The Americans led the Spanish by only one point after three quarters, but James scored on a dunk and then a three-point basket for a 102\u201393 lead with 1:59 to play. James had 19 points in the game, joining [[Michael Jordan]] as the only players to win the [[NBA Most Valuable Player Award|NBA regular-season Most Valuable Player]] (MVP) award, [[NBA Finals|NBA championship]], [[NBA Finals MVP]], and Olympic gold in the same year.<ref name=ap_spain/> Durant added 30 points, the first 30-point game in an Olympic final in US history.<ref name=stein_spain>{{cite news|last=Stein |first=Marc |title=Team USA as good as gold again |date=August 12, 2012 |work=ESPN.com |url=http://espn.go.com/olympics/summer/2012/basketball/story/_/id/8262102/2012-olympics-team-usa-good-gold-again |archiveurl=https://www.webcitation.org/69sDTFERi?url=http://espn.go.com/olympics/summer/2012/basketball/story/_/id/8262102/2012-olympics-team-usa-good-gold-again |archivedate=August 12, 2012 |url-status=live }}</ref> Spain was led by Pau Gasol with 24 points, including his team's first 13 points in the second half to give them a 71\u201370 lead halfway into the third quarter.<ref name=ap_spain/> Gasol added eight rebounds and seven assists in the game.<ref name=stein_spain/>\n\nSpain also trailed by one after the first half, which included their guard [[Juan Carlos Navarro (basketball)|Juan Carlos Navarro]] scoring 19 of his 21 points. The Spanish kept the game close despite Marc Gasol being called for four fouls in the first quarter and a half.<ref name=stein_spain_ia>{{cite news|last=Stein |first=Marc |title=Instant Analysis: Team USA 107, Spain 100 |date=August 12, 2012 |work=ESPN.com |url=http://espn.go.com/blog/olympics/post/_/id/3486/instant-analysis-team-usa-107-spain-100 |archiveurl=https://www.webcitation.org/69sDH3Y1U?url=http://espn.go.com/blog/olympics/post/_/id/3486/instant-analysis-team-usa-107-spain-100 |archivedate=August 12, 2012 |url-status=live }}</ref> James, who frequently guarded one of the Gasols due to the Americans' lack of big men, went to the bench with 7:23 in the game after his fourth foul before returning for the final five minutes.<ref name=stein_spain/><ref name=cacciola/> Bryant had 17 in the game for Team USA, and Love contributed nine points and nine rebounds.<ref name=stein_spain/> The final margin of seven points was the second-closest Olympic final ever after the [[Soviet Union national basketball team|Soviet Union]]'s controversial one-point defeat of the United States in [[1972 Olympic Men's Basketball Final|1972]].<ref name=stein_spain_ia/>\n\n===Statistics===\n{| class=\"toccolours\" style=\"font-size:90%; white-space:nowrap\"\n!colspan=\"6\" style=\"background-color:#F2F2F2; border: 1px solid #AAAAAA\"|Legend\n|-\n|width=\"30px\" style=\"text-align:center; background-color:#F2F2F2; border:1px solid black\"|GP\n|width=\"150px\"|Games played\n|width=\"30px\" style=\"text-align:center; background-color:#F2F2F2; border:1px solid black\"|GS\n|width=\"150px\"|Games started\n|width=\"30px\" style=\"text-align:center; background-color:#F2F2F2; border:1px solid black\"|MPG\n|width=\"150px\"|Minutes per game\n|-\n|style=\"text-align:center; background-color:#F2F2F2; border:1px solid black\"|FGM\n|[[Field goal (basketball)|Field goals]] made\n|style=\"text-align:center; background-color:#F2F2F2; border:1px solid black\"|FGA\n|Field goals attempted\n|style=\"text-align:center; background-color:#F2F2F2; border:1px solid black\"|FG%\n|Field goal percentage\n|-\n|style=\"text-align:center; background-color:#F2F2F2; border:1px solid black\"|3PM\n|[[Three-point field goal|3-point field goals]] made\n|style=\"text-align:center; background-color:#F2F2F2; border:1px solid black\"|3PA\n|3-point field goals attempted\n|style=\"text-align:center; background-color:#F2F2F2; border:1px solid black\"|3P%\n|3-point field goal percentage\n|-\n|style=\"text-align:center; background-color:#F2F2F2; border:1px solid black\"|FTM\n|[[Free throws]] made\n|style=\"text-align:cen