ge Church''\n|<ref>[http://canmore.rcahms.gov.uk/en/site/168154/details/glasgow+blackfriars+chapel/ Site Record for Glasgow, Blackfriars Chapel Black Friars; Old College Church Details]</ref> {{coord|55.8585809|-4.2402023|format=dms|region:GB_type:landmark_source:enwiki|name=Glasgow Blackfriars}}\n|- valign=top\n|Glasgow Franciscan Friary\n|\n|'''Franciscan Friars'''\n|''Roman Catholic Church Of Saint Luke'';<br />''Blessed John Duns Franciscan Friary''\n|<ref>[http://canmore.rcahms.gov.uk/en/site/159794/details/glasgow+gorbals+270+ballater+street+st+luke+s+roman+catholic+church/ Site Record for Glasgow, Gorbals, 270 Ballater Street, St Luke's Roman Catholic Church Roman Catholic Church Of Saint Luke; Blessed John Duns Franciscan Friary; Commercial Road Details]</ref> {{coord|55.8496621|-4.2463714|format=dms|region:GB_type:landmark_source:enwiki|name=Glasgow Franciscan Friary}}\n|- valign=top\n|Glasgow Greyfriars <sup>#</sup>\n|\n|'''Observant Franciscan Friars'''<br />''founded'' 1473-9 (1477, 1472), mistakenly attributed to the archbishop;<br />''dissolved'' or ''secularised'' 1566/7\n|Church of [[St Mary|The Blessed Virgin Mary]]\n|<ref>[http://canmore.rcahms.gov.uk/en/site/44092/details/glasgow+franciscan+friary/ Site Record for Glasgow, Franciscan Friary City Science Centre; Greyfriars Friary Details]</ref> {{coord|55.8604234|-4.2422462|format=dms|region:GB_type:landmark_source:enwiki|name=Glasgow Greyfriars}}\n|- valign=top\n|''Glasgow Dominican Priory''\n|colspan=2|'''''Dominican nuns'''''<br />proposed foundation: bequeathal by Roland Blacadyr \u2014 ''foundation never implemented''\n|St Catherine of Siena\n|\n|- valign=top\n|Govan Monastery\n|\n|traditionally ''founded'' late-6thC by Constantine&nbsp;\u2014 ''evidence lacking''\n|\n|\n|}\n\n[[List of monastic houses in Scotland#top|Return to top of page]]\n\n===Highland Region===\n\n{|width=99% class=\"wikitable\"\n!width = 15%|Foundation\n!width = 5%|Image\n!width = 30%|Communities & provenance\n!width = 2