chaffray Abbey|Inchaffray]]\n|<ref>[http://canmore.rcahms.gov.uk/en/site/26164/details/inchaffray+abbey/ Site Record for Inchaffray Abbey Insula Missarum; Isle Of Masses; Inis Aifreen Details]</ref> {{coord|56.383273|-3.6959204|format=dms|type:landmark_region:GB|name=Inchaffray Abbey}}\n|- valign=top\n|''Kinkell 'Cell' ''\n|colspan=4|'''Augustinian Canons Regular'''<br />asserted cell of Inchaffray; actually parochial church\n|- valign=top\n|Kinkell Commandery\n|\n|'''Knights Hospitaller''' \u2014 ''traditional \u2013 no evidence''\n|\n|\n|- valign=top\n|[[Loch Tay Priory]]\n|\n|'''Augustinian Canons Regular'''&nbsp;\u2014 from [[Scone Abbey|Scone]]<br />''uncertain foundation'';<br />island ''granted'' to Scone by [[Alexander I of Scotland|Alexander I]] 1122\n|The Priory Church of [[St Mary|Saint Mary]], [[Loch Tay]]\n|<ref>[http://canmore.rcahms.gov.uk/en/site/24932/details/loch+tay+priory+island/ Site Record for Loch Tay, Priory Island Eilean Nam Ban; Sybilla's Island; Isle Of Loch Tay Details]</ref> {{coord|56.5839458|-4.0103316|format=dms|type:landmark_region:GB|name=Loch Tay Priory}}\n|- valign=top\n|Methven Monastery\n|\n|'''secular priests'''<br />''founded'' between 1214 and 1223?\n|\n|\n|- valign=top\n|Montrose Blackfriars\n|\n|'''Dominican Friars'''<br />''founded'' 1230, purportedly by Sir Alan Durward;<br />apparently ''abandoned'' after being ''destroyed'' 14thC;<br />secularised 1570/1, revenues ''granted'' to the Burgh of Montrose by [[James VI of Scotland|James VI]] 1 January 1570/1\n|The Nativity of the Blessed Virgin Mary<br />____________________<br />''Blackfriars Hospital''\n|<ref>[http://canmore.rcahms.gov.uk/en/site/36232/details/montrose+dominican+friary/ Site Record for Montrose, Dominican Friary Blackfriars Hospital Details]</ref> {{coord|56.7132802|-2.4773097|format=dms|type:landmark_region:GB|name=Montrose Blackfriars}}\n|- valign=top\n|[[Muthill Monastery]]\n|\n|'''Culdees'''<br />''founded'' between 1178 and 1195;<br />''dissolved'' by