y|Dryburgh]]\n|<ref>[http://canmore.rcahms.gov.uk/en/site/55618/details/dryburgh+abbey/ Site Record for Dryburgh Abbey Details]</ref> {{coord|55.5772803|-2.6494968|format=dms|region:GB_type:landmark_source:enwiki|name=Dryburgh Abbey}}\n|- valign=top\n|[[Fogo Priory]]\n|[[File:Fogo Kirk - geograph.org.uk - 1188284.jpg|150px]]\n|'''Tironensian monks'''&nbsp;\u2014 from [[Kelso Abbey|Kelso]]<br />''dependent on'' Kelso;<br />''founded'' between 1259 and 1297, church of St Nicholas ''granted'' to Kelso by Patrick Corbet;<br />''dissolution unknown''\n|\n|<ref>[http://canmore.rcahms.gov.uk/en/site/58484/details/fogo+st+nicholas+chapel/ Site Record for Fogo, St Nicholas' Chapel Details]</ref> {{coord|55.7356402|-2.3637611|format=dms|region:GB_type:landmark_source:enwiki|name=Fogo Priory}}\n|- valign=top\n|[[Jedburgh Abbey]]\n|[[File:Jedburgh Abbey01.jpg|150px]]\n|land ''granted'' by Ecgred, Bishop of Lindisfarne ''c.''830;<br />'''Augustinian Canons Regular'''&nbsp;\u2014 apparently from St-Quentin, Beauvais<br />priory ''founded c.''1138 (1148) by [[David I of Scotland|David I]] with the assistance of [[John Capellanus|John]], Bishop of Glasgow;<br />''erroneously referred to as Cluniac in one manuscript'';<br />raised to abbey status ''c.''1154;<br />''dissolved'' or ''secularised'' 1696;<br />([[Historic Scotland|HS]])\n|The Abbey Church of [[St Mary|Saint Mary]], [[Jedburgh Abbey|Jedburgh]]\n|<ref>[http://canmore.rcahms.gov.uk/en/site/57020/details/jedburgh+abbey/ Site Record for Jedburgh Abbey Jedburgh, Augustinian Abbey Of St Mary Details]</ref> {{coord|55.4766524|-2.5546753|format=dms|region:GB_type:landmark_source:enwiki|name=Jedburgh Abbey}}\n|- valign=top\n|Jedburgh Blackfriars\n|\n|locally but inaccurately cited '''Dominican Friars'''<ref group=\"note\" name=\"JedburghBlackfriars\">Jedburgh Blackfriars&nbsp;\u2014 included in Dumfries lists</ref><ref group=\"note\" name=\"JedburghBlackfriars1\">Jedburgh Blackfriars&nbsp;\u2014 Watson, ''History of the Francisca