ona \u2014 ''no evidence of monastic foundation''\n|\n|\n|- valign=top\n|Irvine Whitefriars\n|\n|'''Carmelite Friars'''<br />probably ''founded'' before 1293 by a Fullerton of Fullerton;<br />''dissolved'' or ''secularised'' 1572; ''granted'' to the Royal School of Irvine by [[James VI of Scotland|James VI]] 8 June 1572\n|\n|<ref>[http://canmore.rcahms.gov.uk/en/site/41956/details/irvine+fullarton/ Site Record for Irvine, Fullarton Details]</ref> {{coord|55.612693|-4.6736814|format=dms|type:landmark_region:GB|name=Irvine Whitefriars}}\n|- valign=top\n|[[Kilwinning Abbey]]\n|[[File:Kilwinning Abbey - 2 - April 2008.jpg|150px]]\n|'''Tironensian monks'''&nbsp; from [[Kelso Abbey|Kelso]]<br />''founded'' between 1162 and 1189;<br />''dissolved'' 1592\n|The Abbey Church of [[St Mary|the Blessed Virgin Mary]], and Saint Winning, [[Kilwinning]]\n|<ref>[http://canmore.rcahms.gov.uk/en/site/42113/details/kilwinning+abbey/ Site Record for Kilwinning Abbey Details<!-- Bot generated title -->]</ref><ref>[http://www.kilwinning.org/abbey/default.htm Kilwinning Abbey, Kilwinning<!-- Bot generated title -->]</ref> {{coord|55.6534215|-4.6986508|format=dms|type:landmark_region:GB|name=Kilwinning Abbey}}\n|- valign=top\n|Kilwinning Convent\n|\n|Situated at [[Stanecastle]] and mentioned in several charters\n|\n|\n|- valign=top\n|Southannan Priory\n|\n|'''Franciscan nuns'''<br />spurious charter of William, Lord Semple;<br />purportedly reduced to ashes at the Reformation; ''supposed foundation \u2013 spurious provenance''; only chapel of St Anandi and graveyard chantry mentioned at the site\n|\n|<ref>[http://www.britishlistedbuildings.co.uk/sc-14311-ruin-of-old-abbey-southannan-fairlie-west Ruin of Old Abbey Southannan, Fairlie - West Kilbride - North Ayrshire - Scotland | British Listed Buildings]</ref>\n|}\n\n[[List of monastic houses in Scotland#top|Return to top of page]]\n\n=====[[North Ayrshire|Ayrshire, North]] non-Christian monasteries=====\n\n{|width=99% class=\"wikitable\"\n!