iory|Wenlock]], [[List of monastic houses in Shropshire|Shropshire]]<br />priory ''founded c.''1169 (1163);<br />raised to abbey status 1219 (1245);<br />''dissolved'' 1587;<br />([[Church of Scotland|CS]])\n|The Abbey Church of saints [[St Mary|Mary]], [[James, son of Zebedee|James]], [[Saint Mirin|Mirin]] and [[Milburga of Wenlock|Milburga]]\n|<ref>[http://canmore.rcahms.gov.uk/en/site/43139/details/paisley+abbey/ Site Record for Paisley Abbey Abbey Close, Paisley Abbey; Abercorn Aisle Details]</ref><ref>[http://www.paisleyabbey.org.uk/ Paisley Abbey]</ref> {{coord|55.8448677|-4.4203448|format=dms|region:GB_type:landmark_source:enwiki|name=Paisley Abbey}}\n|- valign=top\n|Renfrew Priory\n|\n|'''Cluniac monks'''&nbsp;\u2014 from [[Cluny Abbey|Cluny]]<br />''founded c.''1163;<br />''dissolved'' between 1169 and 1173\n|\n|<ref>[http://canmore.rcahms.gov.uk/en/site/44174/details/renfrew/ Site Record for Renfrew Details]</ref> {{coord|55.8731801|-4.3812758|format=dms|region:GB_type:landmark_source:enwiki|name=Renfrew Priory}}\n|}\n\n[[List of monastic houses in Scotland#top|Return to top of page]]\n\n===Scottish Borders===\n\n{|width=99% class=\"wikitable\"\n!width = 15%|Foundation\n!width = 5%|Image\n!width = 30%|Communities & provenance\n!width = 20%|Formal name or dedication <br />& ''alternative names''\n!width = 10%|Online references & location\n|- valign=top\n|Ancrum Preceptory\n|\n|'''Knights Hospitaller'''<br />purported preceptory or hospital - ''conjectural'' (secular foundation at Ancrum Spittal)\n|\n|\n|- valign=top\n|''Ancrum Red Friars''\n|\n|'''Trinitarians'''<br />supposed house<ref group=\"note\" name=\"AncrumRedFriars\">Ancrum Red Friars&nbsp;\u2014 Geographical Collections relating to Scotland made by Walter Macfarlane (SHS, 1906-08), iii, p.158</ref> \u2014 ''evidence lacking''\n|\n|\n|- valign=top\n|Berwick Austin Friars\n|colspan=4| Formerly located in Scotland until [[Capture of Berwick (1482)]]. See [[List of monastic houses in Northumberland]]\